{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7f0ff3aa-8816-4c83-a7ba-b7e039a38190","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n1. **Update NuGet packages:**\n   - Update `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v4.6.0+** (you already have this ✅)\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n   - Add **`Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild`**\n\n2. **Set the test platform in your `.csproj`:**\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** with the same command:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- NUnit3TestAdapter 4.6.0+ has built-in support for Microsoft.Testing.Platform — no extra NUnit-specific adapter package is needed.\n- The `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild` package bridges `dotnet test` to the new platform.\n- If you use `dotnet test` CLI flags like `--filter`, they still work, but some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` options may need adjustment.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3efda71a-f0d7-4043-a5a3-bdad7f4e76b5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a general knowledge question - I don't need to explore any codebase. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":338,"requestId":"1BED:2F4A2A:2029AD6:2387964:6A03CDB9"},"id":"9f6d0683-4d29-4b59-8b4c-a4e06e4dca31","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:02:59.469Z","parentId":"b12c5590-6e6d-4fbe-ac66-27660aa39abd"}
